content.problemStatement:
- Writing to a CSV file in C++ involves using the `ofstream` class from the `` header.
- Data is typically written row by row, with fields separated by commas.
- You should always check if the file opened successfully before writing.
- After writing, close the file to ensure all data is saved properly.

---

**Example:** Writing Data to a CSV File in C++

```cpp
#include 
#include 
using namespace std;

int main() {
    // Create an output file stream
    ofstream file("data.csv");

    // Check if the file opened successfully
    if (file.is_open()) {
        // Write header
        file << "Name,Age,City\n";

        // Write data rows
        file << "Alice,30,New York\n";
        file << "Bob,25,Los Angeles\n";
        file << "Charlie,28,Chicago\n";

        // Close the file
        file.close();

        cout << "Data written to data.csv successfully.\n";
    } else {
        cout << "Failed to open the file.\n";
    }

    return 0;
}

